through the potency and success of this merit
Here the Realised One has arisen in the world the Worthy One the Perfect Sambuddha
and has taught the Dhamma which leads out which is peaceful
which leads to Nibbāna goes to Awakening and is declared by the Happy One
After hearing the Dhamma we understand it thus
birth is suffering also old age is suffering also death is suffering
also grief lamentation pain sorrow and despair is suffering
also being joined to what is not liked is suffering
also being parted from what is liked is suffering
also not to obtain that which one longs for is suffering
in brief the five components of mind and body that provide fuel for attachment are suffering
They are as follows
The bodilyform component that provides fuel for attachment
the feelings component that provides fuel for attachment
the perceptions component that provides fuel for attachment
the volitions component that provides fuel for attachment
the consciousness component that provides fuel for attachment
For whoever could understand while living the Fortunate One
guided his disciples many times
and this part of the Fortunate Ones instruction to his disciples
he many times repeated
Form is impermanent feelings are impermanent perceptions are impermanent
volitions are impermanent consciousness is impermanent
Form is not self feelings are not self perceptions are not self
volitions are not self consciousness is not self
All conditioned things are impermanent
All things are without a self
We are overcome
by birth old age death grief lamentation pain sorrow and despair
we are overcome by suffering we are afflicted with suffering
May the ending of this entire
mass of suffering become clear
Although the Fortunate One has attained Nibbāna long ago
on account of the Worthy One the Perfect Sambuddha
we have gone forth out of faith from the home to the homeless life
We practice the spiritual life under the Fortunate One
Endowed with the monastic training and livelihood
 may this spiritual life leads us to the end
of the entire mass of suffering
Although the Fortunate One has attained Nibbāna long ago
we have gone for refuge to the Dhamma and the monastic Saṅgha
the Fortunate Ones dispensation
we apply our minds as far as we remember as far as we are able to following the path
 may this path leads us to the end
of the entire mass of suffering
Wholesome thoughts unwholesome thoughts thoughts without consequences
What are wholesome thoughts
When a wholesome thought in the sensuous worlds has arisen
connected with wellbeing joined with knowledge
taking form as object or sound as object
or smell as object or taste as object
or touch as object or thought as object
or whatever it begins with
at that time there is contact balance
At that time these or other
formless thoughts are conditionally originated
These are wholesome thoughts
There are five components
The bodilyform component the feelings component
the perceptions component the volitions component the consciousness component
Herein what is the bodilyform component
Whatever bodilyform there is in the past future or present
internal or external
gross or fine
inferior or excellent
whether far or near
after gathering these together collectively and briefly
This is called the bodilyform component
The compiled and the uncompiled
the uncollected with the collected
the collected with the uncollected
the collected with the collected
the uncollected with the uncollected
the joined and the parted
the parted with the joined
with the parted the joined and the uncollected
There are six designations
the designation of the components the designation of the sensespheres the designation of the elements
the designation of the truths the designation of the faculties the designation of the persons
In what way is there a designation of the person regarding persons
One free occasionally one free always
one unsteady one steady
one liable to fall one not liable to fall
one able in intention one able in guarding
the worldling the lineageholder
one abstaining through fear one not abstaining through fear
one able to arrive one unable to arrive
one determined one undetermined one pathattained one established in fruition
the Worthy One the one on the path to Worthiness
Is a person found in a real and ultimate way
That which is real and ultimate
is this person found in the same real and ultimate way
Acknowledge the refutation
If a person is found in a real and ultimate way
then you surely should have said That which is real and ultimate
this person is found in the same real and ultimate way
Your view is wrong
Whatever are wholesome things are they all wholesome roots
Whatever are wholesome roots are they all wholesome things
Whatever are wholesome things do they all have the same roots with the wholesome root
Whatever have the same roots with the wholesome root are they all wholesome roots
